The paper deals with power allocation in multiple access channels, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also analyzes a non-cooperative game, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The use of distributed learning schemes and local information suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI). The study of equilibrium points and convergence also suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of replicator dynamics is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG).
